<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Collectd on Tech Notebook</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/docs/servers/monitoring/collectd/</link><description>Recent content in Collectd on Tech Notebook</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 01 May 2025 20:33:41 +0200</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://wiki.deimos.fr/docs/servers/monitoring/collectd/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Observium: An Advanced Interface for Collectd</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Observium_:_Une_interface_%C3%A9volu%C3%A9e_pour_Collectd/</link><pubDate>Thu, 22 Mar 2012 15:56:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Observium_:_Une_interface_%C3%A9volu%C3%A9e_pour_Collectd/</guid><description>&lt;p>










&lt;img src="https://wiki.deimos.fr/images/observium-logo.png" alt="Observium" loading="lazy">

&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://www.observium.org" rel="external" target="_blank">Observium&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a> is a graphically oriented monitoring tool similar to &lt;a href="">Munin&lt;/a>. The advantage of this solution is that it manages &lt;a href="">RRD&lt;/a> graphs from &lt;a href="">Collectd&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Since today, a high-performance graphical interface is really something that&amp;rsquo;s missing from &lt;a href="">Collectd&lt;/a>, it would be a shame to have such a powerful solution without an equally capable interface. That&amp;rsquo;s why after much research, I finally came across &lt;a href="https://www.observium.org" rel="external" target="_blank">Observium&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a> which meets this need.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Visage: A Web Interface for Collectd</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Visage_:_Une_interface_web_pour_Collectd/</link><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jun 2011 15:40:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Visage_:_Une_interface_web_pour_Collectd/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://auxesis.github.com/visage/" rel="external" target="_blank">Visage&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a> is currently the best interface for &lt;a href="https://wiki.deimos.fr/Collectd_:_Installation_et_configuration_de_Collectd/">Collectd&lt;/a>. It still needs many new features, but at present it&amp;rsquo;s a superb interface that allows comparative analysis between metrics.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Collectd: Installation and Configuration</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Collectd_:_Installation_et_configuration_de_Collectd/</link><pubDate>Wed, 06 Oct 2010 08:20:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Collectd_:_Installation_et_configuration_de_Collectd/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Collectd gathers statistics about the system it is running on and stores this information. Those statistics can then be used to find current performance bottlenecks (i.e. performance analysis) and predict future system load (i.e. capacity planning). Or if you just want pretty graphs of your private server and are fed up with some homegrown solution you&amp;rsquo;re at the right place, too ;).&lt;/p>
&lt;p>After this installation, you&amp;rsquo;ll likely want access through a web interface. Feel free to continue with &lt;a href="https://wiki.deimos.fr/Serveurs.html#Collectd" rel="external" target="_blank">these documentations&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Heymon: A Web Interface for Collectd</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Heymon_:_Une_interface_web_pour_Collectd/</link><pubDate>Wed, 28 Jul 2010 15:03:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Heymon_:_Une_interface_web_pour_Collectd/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://github.com/newobj/heymon" rel="external" target="_blank">Heymon&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a> is one of the most advanced interfaces currently available for Collectd. In my opinion, it&amp;rsquo;s complementary to other interfaces since it allows comparisons between different machines. However, it&amp;rsquo;s quite complicated to set up.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Jarmon: A Web Interface for Collectd</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Jarmon_:_Une_interface_web_pour_Collectd/</link><pubDate>Tue, 27 Jul 2010 14:12:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Jarmon_:_Une_interface_web_pour_Collectd/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Jarmon is another interface for Collectd. I like this one because it&amp;rsquo;s clean and allows zooming. However, at the moment it only works on a host-by-host basis. This means that in the configuration, you need to specify a particular host.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="installation">Installation &lt;a href="#installation" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>For the installation, we need a web server:&lt;/p>



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="7e3637e" class="language-bash ">
 &lt;code>aptitude install apache2 bzr&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;h2 id="configuration">Configuration &lt;a href="#configuration" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Let&amp;rsquo;s retrieve the source code:&lt;/p>



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="b71002a" class="language-bash ">
 &lt;code>mkdir -p /var/www/
cd /var/www
bzr branch lp:~richardw/jarmon/trunk
mv trunk jarmon
chown -Rf www-data. jarmon
cd jarmon&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;p>Now we create a symbolic link to the directory containing the RRD files of the machine we want to monitor:&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Collection3: A Web Interface for Collectd</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Collection3_:_Une_interface_web_pour_Collectd/</link><pubDate>Wed, 09 Jun 2010 21:58:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Collection3_:_Une_interface_web_pour_Collectd/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://wiki.deimos.fr/Collectd_:_Installation_et_configuration_de_Collectd/">Collectd&lt;/a> is great, but with a functional web interface, it&amp;rsquo;s even better. We&amp;rsquo;re going to see how to install &lt;a href="https://collectd.org/wiki/index.php/Collection3" rel="external" target="_blank">Collection3&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a>, an interface that isn&amp;rsquo;t necessarily pretty, but is very functional.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>